b.	Direct the Municipal Accountant to establish and record RPT and SET at the beginning of the year based on the certified list of RPT accounts Register/Tax Index for the current year provided by the Municipal Treasurer;

c.	Direct the Municipal Treasurer to prepare a certified list of real property tax delinquencies of all taxpayers as of December 31, 2022 in order to establish the correct RPT and SET Receivables outstanding balances and submit to the Municipal Accountant to serve as a basis for preparing necessary adjusting entries; and

c.	Direct the BAC Secretariat to submit contracts and its attached documents to the Office of the Auditor within five (5) working days in adherence to the provisions of COA Circular No. 2009-001 and Section 9.1 of COA Circular No. 2012-001; 

d.	Direct the Accountant to ensure proper and complete supporting documents are attached to all disbursement vouchers; 

e.	Direct the Municipal Engineer to ensure filling up of complete data in the POs/contracts together with Notice of Award and Notice to Proceed indicating the date of receipt by supplier/contractor signifying his conformity to the terms and conditions of the POs/contracts; and

