We recommended that Management:
Strictly implement in a timely manner locally funded PPAs identified to contain the spread of COVID-19 and to provide basic services to the affected population;
Maximize the utilization of all projects, programs and activities of its mandatory funds in relation to its Annual Budget and strictly implement in the ensuing year PPAs classified as continuing projects;
Include only those PPAs which are feasible and can be completed within the target date of implementation, taking into consideration the priorities of the LGU leadership;
Closely monitor and supervise PPA implementation so that problems/issues that may arise shall be immediately addressed; and
Mobilize necessary resources to undertake critical, urgent, and appropriate disaster response aid and measures in a safe and timely manner to curtail and eliminate the threat of COVID-19.

We recommended that Management:
Instruct the General Services Officer-Designate to maintain property cards following the prescribed procedures in property recording and maintain accurate and complete property records;
Assign additional personnel for the inventory committee, if needed;
Conduct annual reconciliation of PPE between the Municipal Accountant Office and the General Services Office records and cause adjustment in the books of accounts and the property records respectively, as warranted, after reconciliation; and
Continuously reconcile the result of the physical count with the property and accounting records.

